Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water up to the boil with
@salt{0.5%tsp} for the rigatoni. Remove the @confit duck legs{2} from their packaging,
place on a #baking tray{} skin side up and drizzle with a little @oil{a little}. Roast
on the top shelf of your oven until the duck skin is crispy, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces. Pick the @sage{0.5%bunch}
and @thyme{1%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).
Halve the @lemon{0.5}. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(grated with a grater).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium heat. When the pan is hot,
add the onion and cook until soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic, thyme and
3/4 of the sage, cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Next, add the
@chopped tomatoes{1}(finely chopped), @red wine jus paste{1}, @sugar{0.5}, and
@water{200}(for the ragu), stir well to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{},
bring to the boil then reduce the heat and simmer until the sauce has thickened,
~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, when boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200} to the water and cook until
tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan.
Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While everything cooks, pour the @olive oil{1}(for the dressing) and a squeeze of
lemon juice into a #medium bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and leave to
one side. This is your salad dressing. Thinly slice the @radishes{100} and pop it
into the dressing bowl.

Once the duck is cooked, remove it to a #cutting board{} and use a #fork{} to pull
the meat off the bone. Discard the bone. Add the duck to the sauce and stir
together. Bring to the boil and simmer until piping hot. Stir half the
@hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) into the sauce and season if needed with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the drained rigatoni to the ragu and combine well to coat
the pasta.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if the ragu is a bit too thick.

Just before serving, add the @pea shoots{40} to the #bowl{} with the radish and mix
well to coat. Divide your rich Tuscan-style duck ragu and rigatoni between 2 #bowls{}
and sprinkle over the remaining cheese and sage. Serve the peashoot salad alongside.
Enjoy!